Transcription.Text: The fleshpots of Egypt for which Israel sighed. Anyhow, Homer does seem to have known any way of cooking meat except by roasting and boiling. When Achilles gave a Royal feast the principal dish was a grill, which he cooked himself, and he knew how to do it, too: -
